main event: A witness observed a silver and white colored object tumbling in the wind in Houston, Pennsylvania on October 8, 1965.
interesting points: The object was described as having a silver side and a white side, resembling binary metal., It was observed during clear weather conditions with good visibility., The object was estimated to be about 40-50 feet in diameter and approximately 2 miles away., Witness estimated the object's speed to be about 1800 mph., The sighting lasted for approximately 20 seconds and the object moved from north to south.
sighted object: a silver and white colored disc-shaped object
witness description: witness observed the object while watching papers blown by the wind
